{
  "texts": [
    "Since G is (k + 1)-colorable, there exists a k + 1-coloring of G. The authors [18] define the color sequence C = ⟨c 1, c 2,..., c n-k-1 ⟩, where c i is the color corresponding, by the (k+1)-coloring,to the vertex v i in the sequence ⟨v 1, v 2,..., v n-k-1 ⟩ with v i being the only vertex in F i+1 \\F i.",
    "If n = k + 1,the color sequence is empty.",
    "Two new concepts are introduced by [18] in order to characterizef k-path graphs with fixed n by sequences of length n -k + 1.",
    "Given a sequence of integers of length j, C = ⟨a 1, a 2,..., a j ⟩, C is said to be normalized if a 1 = 1 and a i ≤ 1+max(a 1,..., a i-1) for 2 ≤ i ≤ j.",
    "Furthermore, if sequence C satisfies a i ̸ = a i+1 for 1 ≤ i ≤ j -1 is said to be restricted."
  ]
}